# Project Conventions

## Quality gates

Work is not done until all three pass from the repo root:

```bash
yarn typecheck
yarn lint
yarn test
```

## Documentation

Before closing a task, evaluate whether any file in `apps/web/docs/` needs updating to reflect the changes made. If unsure whether an update is warranted, ask the user. If substantial new work was done that has no existing doc home, proactively recommend creating a new doc.

## Git safety

Before deleting any file or directory, check whether it is tracked by git:

```bash
git status --short
```

Never remove untracked files or directories without explicit instruction from the user.

## Type reuse

Prefer extending, picking, or omitting existing types over duplicating them:

```ts
// Prefer
type ReleaseCardProps = Pick<Release, 'releaseName' | 'slug' | 'cover'>
type PartialConfig = Partial<SiteConfig>
type WithoutId = Omit<Release, '_id'>

// Avoid
type ReleaseCardProps = { releaseName: string; slug: string; cover: ... }
```

## String single source of truth

- Route paths → `apps/web/lib/routes.ts` (`SLUG_PATH_BY_TYPE`, `FIXED_PATH_BY_TYPE`)
- Sanity singleton IDs → constants in each schema file (`SITE_SETTINGS_ID`, `RELEASES_PAGE_ID`)
- Any string literal used in two or more places → extract to a named constant
